    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Done. The script is at `gpu_token_capacity.py` and runs against a GPU catalog. Here's the output:\n\n```\nModel: Llama3-8B  |  weights=fp16 (15.0 GiB)  |  KV=fp16 (128 KiB/token)  |  utilization=90%\n\nGPU              VRAM   KV budget    Max tokens  ~ @8k ctx\n----------------------------------------------------------\nV100-16GB        16GB          -- OOM (weights do not fit)\nV100-32GB        32GB      13.8GiB       113,402       13.8\nA10-24GB         24GB       6.6GiB        54,419        6.6\nL40S-48GB        48GB      28.2GiB       231,366       28.2\nA100-40GB        40GB      21.0GiB       172,384       21.0\nA100-80GB        80GB      57.0GiB       467,296       57.0\nH100-80GB        80GB      57.0GiB       467,296       57.0\nH200-141GB      141GB     111.9GiB       917,037      111.9\nB200-192GB      192GB     157.8GiB     1,293,050      157.8\nB300-288GB      288GB     244.2GiB     2,000,838      244.2\n```\n\n**How the number is derived**\n- **KV cache per token** = `2 (K+V) × 32 layers × 8 KV heads × 128 head_dim × 2 bytes` = **128 KiB/token** at FP16. The 8 KV heads (not 32) come from Llama3-8B's grouped-query attention — this is what makes the cache 4× smaller than naive MHA.\n- **Max tokens** = `(VRAM × 0.90 − 15 GiB weights) / 128 KiB`. \"Max tokens\" is the *total* across all concurrent sequences (batch × seq_len), so `~ @8k ctx` is roughly how many 8k-context requests fit at once.\n- V100-16GB can't even hold the 15 GiB of FP16 weights, hence OOM.\n\n**Knobs at the top of the script** (`WEIGHT_DTYPE`, `KV_DTYPE`, `UTILIZATION`) let you switch precisions. E.g. FP8 weights + FP8 KV roughly doubles every token count; the `GPUS` list is easy to extend.\n\nA caveat on assumptions: I treat the marketed VRAM as binary GiB and apply a 0.90 utilization factor (vLLM's default) to leave room for the CUDA context, activations, and allocator fragmentation. Real frameworks will land a bit lower. If you'd prefer a different convention (decimal GB, no utilization haircut, or modeling activation memory explicitly), say so and I'll adjust.\n\nSources:\n- [NVIDIA Data Center GPU Specs comparison — IntuitionLabs](https://intuitionlabs.ai/articles/nvidia-data-center-gpu-specs)\n- [NVIDIA Data Center GPUs Explained (A100→B200) — BentoML](https://www.bentoml.com/blog/nvidia-data-center-gpus-explained-a100-h200-b200-and-beyond)\n- [Meta-Llama-3.1-8B config.json — Hugging Face](https://huggingface.co/NousResearch/Meta-Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct/blob/d10aef7999a2b5ba950ab3974312feeedbfe0b77/config.json)"
